reviews.review_text:
- The Dead were clearly having some fun at this show, and there's some unbelievable energy in it, so that even the mistakes sound hilarious rather than jarring. Everybody is playing so insanely well they can barely contain themselves. One of the craziest tight-sounding jam-clicks I've ever heard in this Playin'.

The insanity continues pretty much throughout the 2nd set, though the sound worsens a bit. Everything is amazing, with the Truckin' & Other One a true gem. 

Sound-wise, this is not really one you want up too loud. There's hardly any bass to be found, though Phil's higher frequencies are nicely audible. The upper midrange is harsh, and the whole thing goes just a bit beyond warm and into muddy. Reminds me of a lot of "good" tapes from 1970. But it's great anyway.
Holy Sunshine! I often realize I prefer ’73 because of ‘Here Comes Sunshine’…and this version exemplifies that preference in full color. Enjoy this great AUD!
